<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-01T14:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-01T14:44:00-05:00" n="406" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.33/124</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JRE1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jeffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-01T16:00:00-03:44">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Uruguayan Minister for Foreign Affairs advises that if American
                                Fleet, which is reported to be in South Atlantic, should call at
                                port of Montevideo, it will be received as a friend and not as a
                                belligerent by the Uruguayan Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_JRE1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jeffery</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>